KwaMsane police are appealing to the public for help in
finding Sambulo Mchunu (6) and Zanamuhla Mchunu (5) of KwaMtholo in Mtubatuba, northern KwaZulu-Natal. Police said the two children went missing on Wednesday, February17
at 1.30 pm. They were last seen at KwaMtholo Primary School. They were wearing their school uniforms, black skirts,
yellow shirts, black jerseys and school shoes with black socks. Sambulo is dark
in complexion and Zanamuhla is light in complexion. The police appealed to anyone with information or knowledge
regarding whereabouts of the children to contact Captain Thusi on 079Â 460
7247 or crime stop on 08600 1011.